## Refactor Phase Complete

**Naming Evaluation**: All names in `cli.ts` (`quotePolicies`, `remainingCaps`, `initialCap`, `remainingCapFor`, `isFollowUp`, `results`) clearly reveal intent. No renames needed.

**Refactoring Applied**: Simplified `remainingCapFor` in `/home/experimenter/experiments/runs/2026-05-22_08-52-17_claim-office-example-mapping_v4.2-shared-context_opus-4-7-portkey-no-thinking/src/cli.ts`.

The previous version stored the initial cap into `remainingCaps` on first read, but the only call site always immediately overwrites that entry with `result.remainingCap` after the claim. The cache `set` inside the helper was therefore dead.

Before:
```ts
function remainingCapFor(policyIndex: number): number {
  const existing = remainingCaps.get(policyIndex);
  if (existing !== undefined) return existing;
  const cap = initialCap(quotePolicies[policyIndex]);
  remainingCaps.set(policyIndex, cap);
  return cap;
}
```

After:
```ts
function remainingCapFor(policyIndex: number): number {
  return remainingCaps.get(policyIndex) ?? initialCap(quotePolicies[policyIndex]);
